+// REACHABILITY: start at a clean 0.5/0.5 pool, then drift the weights off 0.5 using ONLY the
+// production per-block emission injection (`adjust_protocol_liquidity`, exactly as run_coinbase
+// calls it) — NO artificial skew_pool — and show the exploit then opens up. This proves the
+// skewed-weight precondition arises from normal protocol operation, not a contrived test state.
